1. Download linux kernel source code

2. cd into source code 

3. You have to configure the kernel using 'make menuconfig'.
   Make sure you turn on CONFIG_LOCALVERSION_AUTO=y.

4. Compile kernel using 'make'

5. Need to compile kernel modules using 'make modules'

6. Install modules using 'make modules_install'

7. And finally you have to install built kernel using 'make install'

8. To reflect changes and boot your machine using recently build kernel do reboot and select appropriate kernel version. 

===============================================

Proof : You can redirect 'dmesg' output in file and send it as proof of task. 
	Very first line of 'dmesg' contains the boot information. 
